Moody's Investors Service Inc said itdowngraded Dayton Hudson Corp's 1.3 billion dlrs of debt.    The agency cut to Aa-3 from Aa-2 Dayton Hudson's seniornotes, debentures, revenue bonds and Eurodebt, and shelfregistration to Provisional Aa-3 from Provisional Aa-2.    Moody's said it expected that leverage, which has risenbecause of an aggressive expansion program, would remain highdue to the company's spending plans. The agency noted thatDayton Hudson's operating returns recently declined.    But Moody's also said the company's recent operatingproblems would probably be temporary. Reuter&#3;